A: Owner will indemnify, defend and save Omega harmless from any and all damage, injury, claims, judgments, or any other liabilities whatsoever arising out of the execution and performance of this Contract by Omega (including, but not limited to all fines, fees, costs, expenses and penalties assessed against against Omega), including attorney’s fees therefore, to the extent that all such claims, judgments, or any other liabilities are attributable in whole or in part to Owner’s actions or inactions. Such obligation shall not be construed to negate, abridge, or otherwise reduce any other right or obligation of indemnity which would otherwise exist. Owner's obligation arising out of this Agreement shall survive any termination thereof.
B: OMEGA FIRE & LIFE SAFETY IS NOT AN INSURER; DISCLAIMER OF WARRANTIES; LIMITATION OF LIABILITY: It is understood and agreed: that OMEGA is not an insurer, that insurance shall be obtained by the Customer; that indemnity for any loss, damage and expense arising from the work performed under this contract shall be limited to any insurance coverage only, and Omega is released from any and all liability for all such loss, damage and expense; that the payments provided for herein are based solely on the value of the services as set forth herein and are unrelated to the value of Customer’s property and/or Customer’s implied warranty or merchantability or fitness that the services supplied will avert or prevent occurrences or the consequences thereof which the system or service is designed to detect or avert. Customer acknowledges that it is impractical and extremely difficult to determine the actual damages, including property loss, personal injury or death, if any, which may be proximately the result of Omega's negligence, a failure to perform any of the obligations herein, or the failure of the monitoring service or equipment to properly operate, with resulting loss to Customer because of the following, amongst other things:                                                                                                                                                                                                                              (a) The uncertain amount of value of Customer’s property or the property of others kept on the premises which may be lost, destroyed, damaged, or otherwise affected by occurrences which the system or service is designed to detect or avert; 
(b) The uncertainty of the response time of any police or fire department, paramedic unit or others, should they be dispatched as a result of a signal being received; 
(c) The inability to ascertain what portion, if any, of any property loss, personal injury or death would be proximately caused by OMEGA’s failure to perform or by its equipment to operate; 
(d) The uncertainty of any claim that might be made by Customer against OMEGA; 
(e) The nature of the service to be performed by OMEGA or its subcontractors.                                                                                                                        Customer understands and agrees that if OMEGA should be found liable to Customer for loss or damage to property or persons due to OMEGA’s negligence or failure of OMEGA’s monitoring service or monitoring equipment in any respect whatsoever, OMEGA’s liability shall be limited to an amount not to exceed Five Hundred Dollars (500.00) or the total value of the monitoring services for the year in which a loss or damage to property or persons occurs, whichever is higher, and this liability shall be exclusive; and that the provisions of this Section shall apply if loss or damage, irrespective of cause or origin, results directly or indirectly to persons or property, from performance or non-performance of the obligations imposed by this contract, or from negligence, active or otherwise, OMEGA, its agents, assigns, subcontractors or employees, and/or the monitoring service used by Omega.
